So excited for the release of @duncanlyledance’s “The Golden Fish (pas de deux)” next Monday on Youtube! We had a great time creating this pas with @duncanlyle in the studio and we can’t wait for everyone to watch it starting next Monday 🙌🏼
The Golden Fish is based on the fairytale “The Fisherman and the Fish”— an allegory about the corruption of greed. Galia (Anabel) and Taras (Carlos) are a peasant couple seduced by seemingly unending access to riches. This Pas de Deux from Act 2 shows the couple celebrating their newfound wealth, unaware that their continually escalating demands from the captured magical golden fish will ultimately return them to the poverty from which they began.
Photography and editing by @cydoherty 
Lighting by Kelly Martin.
Costumes by @duncanlyle

Very excited to be debuting as Mercutio in MacMillan’s Romeo and Juliet next week at the @kennedycenter 🙌🏼
I first started learning this role 3 years ago but haven’t been able to perform it until now, first cause of the 2020 pandemic and last year because of my ankle injury.
I’m looking forward to experiencing the whole journey of emotions that this character goes through in the ballet until he dies in Act II. 
Very grateful to be sharing the stage with @thomasforster22 and @christineshevchenko as Romeo and Juliet on 2/17 at 1:30pm and @jamesbwhiteside and @gillianemurphy on 2/18 at 7:30pm. @sungwoohan__ will be playing Benvolio those dates too 🙏🏼

‘The Golden Fish’ Pas de deux out now on Youtube!!! 🙌🏼
Thanks @duncanlyledance for creating such a beautiful and elegant pas de deux on @anabel_katsnelson and I! Link on my bio to watch!! 🙌🏼
Video and editing by the amazing @cydoherty

Incredibly grateful for so many things this week I don’t even know where to start…
Can’t put into words how thankful I am I finally had the chance to dance the role of Mercutio in Macmillan’s Romeo and Juliet 🙏🏼 
To perform at the @kennedycenter again this year was a huge milestone for me on my ankle recovery, physically, but especially mentally. So I feel very proud to know that I’m walking out of here on two feet, unlike last year when I left this theatre on crutches, and for that I feel very accomplished 👏🏼
I wanna thank the whole 3 different casts I performed with for making it so fun and enjoyable. And thank you to my whole @abtofficial family for the support and encouragement along the way. Congratulations to all the other dancers debuting this week and specially to @tylerrrmaloney for sharing this journey with me 🫶🏼

Little throwback to one of my favorite performances ever! Black Swan pas de deux with @skylarbrandt for @hamptonsdanceproject 🙌🏼
This is one of my favorite moments in the pas when Odile bourrées around Siegfried making him rotate around her before the turns 🖤
Happy 26th birthday to this handsome man! For many more years sharing memories together. Thanks for being there for me every step of the way 💙

Thanks for capturing this moment @menegussiphotography and merde everyone!! 🙏🏼

Had the best time ever on stage this past week performing @wheeldony’s “Like Water for Chocolate” at the @segerstromarts 💥
I felt so lucky to be out there with all the wonderful artists of each cast. The energy on stage on every show was incredible, and to all my colleagues and friends out there with me in the Campfire scene, thank you so much for making it so fun and unforgettable 🙏🏼
Grateful to have shared the experience with @catehurlin as Gertrudis. I had a blast every single second I was out there with you. Can’t wait to do it again in the spring 🌟
Congratulations to everyone involved who worked so hard to make it happen, I honestly think we killed it!!!🔥

I had the best time hanging out with this amazing group of friends and artists! Thank you @colabdance and @gemma_bond__ for bringing us all together! Working with you is always a joy and I can’t wait to get back into the studio with you soon 🙌🏼
Very grateful to @vineyardarts for hosting us and letting us use the stunning facilities 🙏🏼

Very excited to revisit this role in @wheeldony’s ‘Like Water for Chocolate’ with my Gertrudis @catehurlin 🔥
@abtofficial season at the @metopera opens next Thursday June 22nd! Do you have your tickets yet?? 🙆🏻‍♂️🙌🏼

Very excited to make my debut as Pedro alongside @skylarbrandt as Tita on @wheeldony’s “Like Water for Chocolate” on Monday June 26th at 7:30pm at the @metopera 🙆🏻‍♂️
Diving into this character has been one of the most rewarding and fun processes I’ve ever been a part to. Story telling ballet have always been my favorite thing to perform and I’m looking forward to this one! Thanks @skylarbrandt for your patience with me and for being a dream partner and thanks @carloslopeznewyork for guiding us through the journey! I seriously cannot wait 🫶🏼

Toningt is the opening night performance of @wheeldony’s “Like Water for Chocolate” 🙌🏼
This will be the first time I perform at the @metopera in 4 years, since I missed the last 3 seasons due to the pandemic and an ankle injury. I’m very excited to be back on this stage performing the role of Juan Alejandrez alongside @catehurlin as Gertrudis 🔥 
We are doing 12 shows so don’t miss it if you have a chance to come see it 🙆🏻‍♂️
.
.
📷: Marty Sohl

06•26•2023
Performing Pedro in @wheeldony’s “Like Water for Chocolate” will forever be one of the most special and fullfilling experiences of my life and my professional career. 
Still trying to find the words to describe all the feelings from that performance. I’m full of happiness and so grateful to so many people 🙏🏼
Thank you @wheeldony for your trust in @skylarbrandt and I and for giving us the opportunity to tell @chocolate.esquivel’s “Como agua para Chocolate” story from Tita’s and Pedro’s perspective.
Thank you @carloslopeznewyork and @jasongrantfowler for your patience and technical and artistic guidance throughout the process of learning the ballet 🙆🏻‍♂️
To my Tita @skylarbrandt for being the most generous, giving and supportive partner I could ever ask for. It was a joy sharing this journey with you and I can’t wait to hopefully do it all over again with you one day 💛
Very grateful to the whole cast and to all my friends and colleagues at @abtofficial for all the support and the love you gave me.
And to the most incredible audience that went on the journey with us cheered us on until the last second 👏🏼

Hasta pronto Juan Alejandrez! Playing the Lead Revolutionary role in @wheeldony’s “Like Water for Chocolate” has been one of the most fullfilling and enjoyable roles I’ve ever done. There was so much room in the choreography to play with it and I felt so much growth each time I performed it. A true gift as an artist to be able to make something your own and do it so differently each time. Very grateful for this one 🙏🏼
Congratulations to everyone for making it through 12 incredible performances and for all the vibrant energy that we brought on stage each night 👏🏼
Thank you to my Gertrudis @catehurlin for being the most present and fun partner in crime out there! It was a blast bringing all that fuego out there with you ❤️🔥
And thanks @e_zordan for taking all these awesome pictures and following us around nighr after night! You’re the best 🙌🏼

Special shoutout to @breannegranlund for finishing up Act I so strong on an injured leg on Tuesday and thank you @erica_lall for stepping in last minute for Act III and for the show Saturday Matinée. And also to @abbeyjess_ for slaying that lead Aristocrat on Saturday 🫶🏼
Thank you @e_zordan for capturing some of these moments in the show 🙏🏼
